introduction: In this video, we discuss a virtual conference that is taking place on February 15th and 22nd, 2023. The conference features an AI product owner track, an engineering track, and handson workshops. Some of the keynote speakers include Jason Louie, Shrea Shanar, Dro, Cameron Wolf, Lauren Lockridge, Tunji, Golden, Kai, Fison, and Jerry Louie. The conference also covers topics such as AI product management, AI platform development, and AI model evaluation.

sections.title: Section 1: Introduction to the Virtual Conference
content: The virtual conference is taking place on February 15th and 22nd, 2023.
The conference features an AI product owner track, an engineering track, and handson workshops.
Some of the keynote speakers include Jason Louie, Shrea Shanar, Dro, Cameron Wolf, Lauren Lockridge, Tunji, Golden, Kai, Fison, and Jerry Louie.
The conference will cover topics such as AI product management, AI platform development, and AI model evaluation.

sections.title: Section 2: AI Product Owner Track
content: The AI product owner track will focus on the role of product owners in the AI industry.
Topics covered in this track will include AI product strategy, AI product development, and AI product management.
Speakers in this track will discuss their experiences in the field and share insights on how to succeed as a product owner in the AI industry.
Attendees of this track will have the opportunity to network with other product owners and learn from industry experts.

sections.title: Section 3: Engineering Track
content: The engineering track will focus on the technical aspects of AI development.
Topics covered in this track will include AI model development, AI model deployment, and AI model evaluation.
Speakers in this track will discuss their experiences in building and deploying AI models and share insights on best practices and challenges in the field.
Attendees of this track will have the opportunity to learn from industry experts and network with other engineers in the AI industry.

sections.title: Section 4: Hands-on Workshops
content: The hands-on workshops will provide attendees with the opportunity to learn by doing.
Workshops will cover topics such as AI model development using popular frameworks, AI model deployment on cloud platforms, and AI model evaluation techniques.
Attendees will have the chance to work on real-world projects and receive feedback from experienced instructors.
Workshops will be held in a collaborative environment, allowing attendees to learn from each other and share their knowledge.

sections.title: Section 5: Keynote Speakers and Topics Covered
